{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/research/existing-app-intake.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Existing App UX Intake\n\n## Source Policy\n- I used only repository files, run context artifacts, local tests, scripts, and local onboarding/wake/app/shell code.\n- No external browsing, competitor scraping, or additional proprietary assets were used.\n- No secrets, credentials, tokens, cookies, private keys, session values, or environment variables were recorded.\n- This intake is scoped to UX observation only and does not assume any behavioral or product-policy changes.\n\n## Source List\n- .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/preflight.json\n- .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/checkout.json\n- apps/waketask-ios/README.md\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/AppRootView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LaunchRouter.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/MainTabView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingContainerView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPage.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPageView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeContent.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeViewModel.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/QuickActionCard.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeDashboardView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeFlowViewModel.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/ProfileView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/ProfileViewModel.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileHeader.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileAccountInfoSection.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileQuickActionsSection.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileAboutSection.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileDangerZoneSection.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/EditProfileSheet.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/SignInView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/EmailLoginView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/EmailSignUpView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/ForgotPasswordView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Auth/EmailSignUpFormFields.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Auth/EmailSignUpViewModel.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LegalDocumentView.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/FeatureCard.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/SubscriptionStatusCard.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Resources/en.lproj/Localizable.strings\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Wake.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Onboarding.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Common.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Auth.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+A11y.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Core/Sources/Core/WakeTask/WakeTaskModels.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Core/Sources/Core/WakeTask/WakeContractEvaluator.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Core/Sources/Core/WakeTask/WakeTaskProtocols.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Core/Sources/Core/WakeTask/DefaultWakeMissionRotationEngine.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/LaunchRouterTests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeViewModelTests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeContentTests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/WakeTask/WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/AppShellSnapshotTests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/AuthFlowUITests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/ChatFlowUITests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/PaywallFlowUITests.swift\n- apps/waketask-ios/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh\n- prompts/iphone-app-factory/ux-existing-app-intake.md\n- .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/research/reference-gap-analysis.json (if present)\n\n## Current App Purpose\nThe app is a wake-up assistant with mission-driven habit support. It guides users from first launch through onboarding, authentication, and an initial home/workspace dashboard where wake tasks are created, run, and reviewed. A chat/history lane is linked into the flow and the app includes support and account/profile sections.\n\n## Current User Flow\n1. Launch route starts at `LaunchRouter`.\n2. If onboarding is incomplete, the app presents a 3-page onboarding modal.\n3. Auth gate appears next with social plus email entry points.\n4. On sign-in success, user lands in root shell with tabs.\n5. Main tabs: Home, Runs, Profile.\n6. Home exposes quick actions and feature/summary cards.\n7. Runs opens wake dashboard and task execution state.\n8. Profile provides account management, help/settings links, legal links, and destructive actions.\n9. Tests/UX scripts include flows for auth, wake run exploration, chat, and paywall.\n\n## Current Screens And States\n- Onboarding: three slides with paging and button flow, skip behavior tied to page state.\n- Sign in and auth: social sign-in + email login/sign-up + forgot-password path.\n- Home: card-based quick actions and feed-like layout via `HomeContent`.\n- Home states: normal actions, empty recent section, and wake onboarding handoff to primary task creation.\n- Runs/Wake dashboard: list/selector, active flow, completion UI, wake-check and escalation controls.\n- Wake flow details: mission state progression, active timer behavior, completion states, and wake-check interactions.\n- Profile: user header/account details, quick account actions, settings-like legal/about/help actions, danger-zone actions.\n- Error/loading states: present in model and tests but not always fully surfaced in the UI.\n- Missing/weakly observed visual evidence: no screenshot pack or simulator captures were found in this run workspace.\n\n## Current App Weaknesses\n- Navigation: onboarding-first gating is rigid; “Runs” label is weakly descriptive versus visible behavior; deep actions are spread across multiple taps; no visible bottom-anchored persistent onboarding summary.\n- Hierarchy: task-first purpose is hidden under generic cards and tab labels; profile legal/help actions compete with operational actions.\n- Copy: strong product positioning onboarding exists, but many production strings are utilitarian or inconsistent across wake states and some copy appears generic template-style.\n- Interaction states: weak empty/loading feedback in some flows; debug-only sign-in path risks production ambiguity; many transitions rely on implicit default states.\n- Accessibility: several controls include accessibility labels, but coverage is partial in profile and dashboard controls.\n- Emotional tone: mostly supportive on goals but can be abrupt in state transitions; there is little emotional continuity between success, failure, and recovery states.\n\n## Protected Existing Systems\n- auth: keep auth providers, entry points, and auth flow wiring out of scope until later ADR approval.\n- payments: keep paywall/subscription and purchase orchestration out of scope until later ADR approval.\n- storage: keep persistence and user data handling out of scope until later ADR approval.\n- networking: keep API/client wiring out of scope until later ADR approval.\n- localization: keep translation keys/strings architecture out of scope until later ADR approval.\n- settings: keep broader settings architecture out of scope until later ADR approval.\n- design system: keep base component architecture out of scope until later ADR approval.\n\n## what_to_adapt\n- Keep the three-stage onboarding + auth-first flow shape because it already produces predictable first-run progression.\n- Keep tab-based task/home/profile separation as a stable mental model.\n- Keep card-driven quick actions and concise goal framing on home.\n- Keep explicit wake mission progression logic and clear active-state signaling.\n- Keep modular view-model/state ownership separation between Home, Wake, and Profile.\n- Keep local accessibility labeling where available and extend rather than replace.\n\n## what_not_to_copy\n- Do not copy hidden or weak debug-only authentication flows.\n- Do not copy placeholder or non-functional links in profile/legal/help as-is.\n- Do not copy under-specified interaction handling where loading, disabled, and failure states are not visible.\n- Do not copy external competitor or App Store patterns without sourcing current evidence and approvals.\n- Do not copy copy that feels generic or emotionally inconsistent with intended journey.\n- Do not copy weak labeling gaps where controls are not fully announced for accessibility.\n\n## Open Questions\n- Which user segments must we optimize for first: new user wake completion vs repeat users with skipped onboarding?\n- Should “Runs” be renamed and restructured for discoverability without disrupting existing telemetry?\n- What emotional voice do we want for failure and fallback states in wake sessions?\n- What level of accessibility depth is required before release: label parity only, or full dynamic announcements and rotor/semantic ordering?\n- Which interaction states must be mandatory for each action path before UX validation (especially paywall-adjacent and error handling)?\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
